Lotto Number Generator

Developer: Karabo Khunou

The Lotto Number Generator is a Java program that allows users to generate unique random numbers within a specified range and quantity of balls. It can be used for various lotto games or number selection tasks.
Features

    Generates unique random numbers within a given range.
    Allows users to specify the number of balls to be selected.
    Ensures that duplicates are not included in the generated numbers.
    Provides a simple and easy-to-use command-line interface.

Getting Started

    Ensure you have Java Development Kit (JDK) installed on your machine.
    Clone or download the Lotto Number Generator repository.
    Open a terminal or command prompt and navigate to the project directory.
    Compile the Java source file: javac LottoNumberGenerator.java
    Run the program: java LottoNumberGenerator

Usage

    Set the desired range and quantity of balls in the main method of the LottoNumberGenerator class.
    Compile and run the program as described in the "Getting Started" section.
    The program will generate and display the unique random numbers.

Example

Let's assume we want to generate 6 unique random numbers within the range of 1 to 49. We would set the following values in the main method:

java

int minNumber = 1;
int maxNumber = 49;
int numberOfBalls = 6;

Upon running the program, it will generate and display the lotto numbers.
